(62, 1, 1, 44, 4, 20, 20, 'which we have heard, which we have seen', 'Connection of Witness and Testimony', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of personal experience in witnessing the truth. They highlight the act of speaking about what has been ''seen and heard,'' underscoring a shared theme of testimony.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 1, 43, 20, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of Physical Experience', 'Both passages emphasize the physical experience of encountering Jesus. In 1 John 1:1, the author speaks of handling ''the Word of life,'' while John 20:27 invites Thomas to touch Jesus'' hands and side.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 1, 62, 4, 14, 14, 'which we have seen', 'Connection of Testimony and Saviour', 'This connection highlights the theme of firsthand experience and testimony regarding Jesus. Both passages emphasize the act of seeing and proclaiming Jesus as the Word of life and the Saviour of the world.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 1, 43, 1, 1, 18, 'the Word', 'Connection of the Word', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''the Word'' as central to the beginning of creation and life. The phrase ''which we have heard'' in 1 John connects to the declaration of the Word''s existence in John 1:1, highlighting the experiential knowledge of the Word made flesh.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 1, 42, 24, 39, 39, NULL, 'Connection of Physical Experience', 'Both passages emphasize the physical experience of handling and seeing Jesus. In 1 John 1:1, the author speaks of having ''handled'' the Word of life, while Luke 24:39 invites the disciples to ''handle me, and see.''', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 1, 61, 1, 16, 18, 'which we have heard, which we have seen', 'Eyewitness Testimony of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of firsthand experience with Jesus. 1 John speaks of what was ''heard'' and ''seen,'' while 2 Peter highlights being ''eyewitnesses'' of His majesty.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 1, 62, 1, 2, 3, 'we have seen', 'Connection of Manifested Life', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of life being manifested and witnessed. The phrase ''we have seen'' links the experiences of the apostles with the declaration of eternal life.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 2, 43, 1, 4, 4, 'the life was manifested', 'Connection of Life and Light', 'This connection highlights the theme of life present in both passages. In 1 John 1:2, the ''life'' is manifested, while in John 1:4, ''life'' is described as the ''light of men.''', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 2, 62, 5, 20, 20, 'eternal life', 'Connection of Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of eternal life, linking the manifestation of life in 1 John 1:2 to the understanding of true life in 1 John 5:20. This connection highlights the continuity of the message regarding the nature of Jesus Christ as eternal life.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 2, 54, 3, 16, 16, 'manifested', 'Manifestation of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of manifestation, as both passages discuss the concept of God being revealed. In 1 John 1:2, the life was ''manifested,'' while 1 Timothy 3:16 states that ''God was manifest in the flesh.''', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 2, 43, 17, 3, 3, 'eternal life', 'Connection of Eternal Life', 'This connection highlights the concept of eternal life as presented in both passages. 1 John 1:2 refers to ''eternal life,'' while John 17:3 defines it as knowing God and Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 2, 56, 1, 2, 2, 'eternal life', 'Connection of Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of eternal life, with 1 John 1:2 presenting it as manifested and witnessed, while Titus 1:2 speaks of it as a promise from God. This connection highlights the continuity of the theme of eternal life across the texts.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 2, 62, 3, 8, 8, 'was manifested', 'Manifestation of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the manifestation of Christ. In 1 John 1:2, the life was manifested, while in 1 John 3:8, the Son of God was manifested to destroy the works of the devil.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 2, 48, 4, 4, 4, 'was manifested', 'Manifestation of Life', 'Both passages emphasize the manifestation of divine life. 1 John speaks of life being manifested, while Galatians highlights the sending of God''s Son, who embodies that life.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 3, 46, 1, 9, 9, 'fellowship with us', 'Fellowship with Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of fellowship with Jesus Christ. 1 John 1:3 speaks of fellowship with the Father and the Son, while 1 Corinthians 1:9 mentions being called unto the fellowship of His Son.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 3, 43, 17, 3, 3, 'fellowship with us', 'Fellowship and Knowledge of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of fellowship with God and Jesus Christ. Both passages emphasize knowing God and having a relationship with Him as essential for eternal life.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 3, 43, 17, 21, 21, 'fellowship with us', 'Fellowship and Unity in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of fellowship among believers and with God. Both passages emphasize the desire for unity, as seen in ''fellowship with us'' and ''that they also may be one in us.''', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 3, 44, 4, 20, 20, 'that ye also may have fellowship with us', 'Connection of Witness and Fellowship', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sharing experiences of what has been seen and heard. This connection highlights the communal aspect of fellowship with others and with God.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 3, 50, 2, 1, 1, 'fellowship with us', 'Fellowship in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of fellowship, with 1 John highlighting fellowship with the Father and Son, while Philippians speaks of fellowship of the Spirit. This connection highlights the communal aspect of faith in Christ.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 3, 47, 13, 14, 14, 'fellowship with us', 'Fellowship and Communion Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of fellowship and communion with God. 1 John 1:3 speaks of fellowship with the Father and Son, while 2 Corinthians 13:14 mentions communion with the Holy Ghost, highlighting a shared spiritual connection.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 3, 58, 3, 14, 14, 'fellowship with us', 'Fellowship and Partaking in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of fellowship with Christ. Both passages emphasize the importance of maintaining a steadfast relationship with Him to fully partake in His life and blessings.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 4, 43, 15, 11, 11, 'that your joy may be full', 'Joy Fulfillment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of joy being made full. 1 John 1:4 states that writing is intended for joy to be full, while John 15:11 expresses that spoken words aim for joy to remain and be full.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 4, 43, 16, 24, 24, 'that your joy may be full', 'Connection of Joy in Prayer', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of joy being made full. In 1 John 1:4, joy is linked to the message being shared, while John 16:24 connects joy to asking in Jesus'' name.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 4, 63, 1, 12, 12, NULL, 'Connection of Joy in Letters', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of joy being made full. In 1 John 1:4, joy is linked to the message being shared, while 2 John 1:12 expresses that joy is completed through personal communication.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 4, 47, 1, 24, 24, 'your joy may be full', 'Connection of Joy in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the role of joy in the believer''s life. 1 John 1:4 speaks of joy being full, while 2 Corinthians 1:24 highlights being helpers of joy, linking the experience of joy to faith.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 4, 35, 3, 17, 18, 'that your joy may be full', 'Joy in Adversity', 'This connection highlights the theme of joy despite circumstances. While 1 John 1:4 speaks of full joy, Habakkuk 3:17-18 expresses joy in the Lord despite dire situations.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 4, 49, 3, 19, 19, 'your joy may be full', 'Joy and Fulness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being filled. Both passages emphasize a state of fullness, with 1 John mentioning joy and Ephesians referring to the fullness of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 4, 23, 61, 10, 10, 'that your joy may be full', 'Joy and Salvation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize joy as a response to God''s salvation. In 1 John, the fullness of joy is linked to the message of salvation, while Isaiah expresses joy in God for being clothed with salvation and righteousness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 5, 43, 8, 12, 12, 'God is light', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of light as a representation of God and Jesus. 1 John 1:5 states that ''God is light,'' while John 8:12 declares Jesus as ''the light of the world,'' linking their divine nature and the absence of darkness.', 'theme', 0.853, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 5, 59, 1, 17, 17, 'God is light', 'Connection of Light and Gifts', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of God as light. 1 John 1:5 states, ''God is light,'' while James 1:17 refers to ''the Father of lights.'' This connection highlights the consistent biblical theme of God''s purity and goodness.', 'theme', 0.657, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 5, 23, 60, 19, 19, 'God is light', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of God as light. In 1 John, God is described as light with no darkness, while Isaiah presents the Lord as an everlasting light, replacing earthly sources of light.', 'theme', 0.608, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 5, 19, 27, 1, 1, 'God is light', 'God as Light and Strength', 'Both passages emphasize God as light, symbolizing guidance and safety. In 1 John, God is described as light with no darkness, while Psalms portrays the Lord as light and strength, instilling confidence against fear.', 'theme', 0.587, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 5, 43, 1, 9, 9, 'God is light', 'Connection of Light Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of light, with 1 John stating that ''God is light'' and John identifying Jesus as ''the true Light.'' This connection highlights the theme of divine illumination present in both texts.', 'theme', 0.552, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 5, 66, 22, 5, 5, 'God is light', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of God as light, contrasting with darkness. In 1 John, God is described as light with no darkness, while Revelation depicts a future without night, highlighting God''s illuminating presence.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 5, 66, 21, 23, 23, 'God is light', 'God as Light in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of God as light in both passages. 1 John 1:5 states, ''God is light,'' while Revelation 21:23 describes God''s glory as the source of light in the city.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 6, 62, 4, 20, 20, 'we lie, and do not the truth', 'Connection of Truth and Love', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of truthfulness in relation to one''s actions. The first verse highlights that claiming fellowship with God while walking in darkness is a lie, while the second verse states that claiming to love God while hating one''s brother is also a lie. This connection highlights the importance of genuine love and truth in one''s relationship with God and others.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 6, 62, 2, 4, 4, 'we lie, and do not the truth', 'Fellowship and Commandments Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of truth in relation to one''s actions. Both passages emphasize that claiming to know God or have fellowship with Him is contradicted by failing to live according to His commandments.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 6, 43, 3, 19, 21, 'fellowship with him, and walk in darkness', 'Fellowship and Light vs. Darkness', 'This connection highlights the contrast between walking in darkness and coming to the light. Both passages emphasize the importance of truth and the rejection of evil deeds associated with darkness.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 6, 20, 4, 18, 19, 'walk in darkness', 'Light and Darkness Contrast', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between light and darkness. 1 John 1:6 speaks of walking in darkness, while Proverbs 4:18-19 describes the path of the just as a shining light, illustrating the moral implications of one''s spiritual walk.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 6, 20, 2, 13, 13, 'walk in darkness', 'Walking in Darkness', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of walking in darkness as a departure from truth and uprightness. This connection highlights the moral implications of choosing paths that lead away from righteousness.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 6, 43, 8, 12, 12, 'walk in darkness', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between walking in darkness and having light. 1 John 1:6 warns against claiming fellowship while in darkness, while John 8:12 promises light to those who follow Jesus.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 6, 47, 6, 14, 16, 'fellowship with him, and walk in darkness', 'Fellowship and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between light and darkness, highlighting the incompatibility of fellowship with God and walking in darkness. They also stress the importance of maintaining righteousness and avoiding associations with unbelievers.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 7, 49, 5, 8, 8, 'walk in the light', 'Walking in the Light', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of walking in the light. 1 John 1:7 mentions walking in the light and having fellowship, while Ephesians 5:8 encourages believers to walk as children of light.', 'theme', 0.881, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 7, 45, 13, 12, 12, 'walk in the light', 'Light and Darkness Contrast', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between light and darkness. 1 John 1:7 speaks of walking in the light, while Romans 13:12 encourages casting off works of darkness and putting on the armour of light.', 'theme', 0.608, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 7, 66, 1, 5, 5, 'the blood of Jesus Christ his Son cleanseth us from all sin', 'Connection of Cleansing by Blood', 'Both passages emphasize the cleansing from sin through the blood of Jesus. 1 John 1:7 mentions that the blood of Jesus cleanses us from all sin, while Revelation 1:5 states that he washed us from our sins in his own blood.', 'theme', 0.601, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 7, 49, 1, 7, 7, 'the blood of Jesus Christ his Son cleanseth us from all sin', 'Connection of Redemption and Forgiveness', 'Both passages emphasize the cleansing and forgiveness of sins through the blood of Jesus. 1 John 1:7 mentions the cleansing from all sin, while Ephesians 1:7 highlights redemption and forgiveness according to grace.', 'theme', 0.566, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 7, 58, 9, 14, 14, 'the blood of Jesus Christ his Son cleanseth us from all sin', 'Connection of Christ''s Cleansing Blood', 'Both passages emphasize the cleansing power of the blood of Christ. 1 John 1:7 speaks of the blood cleansing from all sin, while Hebrews 9:14 highlights its role in purging the conscience to serve God.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 7, 62, 2, 9, 10, 'walk in the light', 'Connection of Light and Love', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of walking in the light and loving one another. The first passage associates walking in the light with fellowship and cleansing from sin, while the second passage connects being in the light with loving one''s brother, indicating that true light manifests in love.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 7, 66, 7, 14, 14, 'the blood of Jesus Christ his Son cleanseth us from all sin', 'Connection of Cleansing by Blood', 'Both passages emphasize the cleansing power of the blood of Jesus. 1 John 1:7 speaks of being cleansed from all sin, while Revelation 7:14 refers to those who have washed their robes in the blood of the Lamb.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 8, 45, 3, 23, 23, 'we have no sin', 'Sin and Human Condition', 'Both passages emphasize the reality of sin in human life. 1 John 1:8 suggests self-deception about sin, while Romans 3:23 states that all have sinned, reinforcing the universal nature of this condition.', 'theme', 0.6499999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 8, 21, 7, 20, 20, NULL, 'Sinfulness of Humanity', 'Both passages emphasize the universal nature of sin among humanity. 1 John 1:8 highlights self-deception regarding sin, while Ecclesiastes 7:20 states that no just man is without sin.', 'theme', 0.601, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 8, 59, 3, 2, 2, NULL, 'Sin and Offense in Speech', 'Both passages emphasize the reality of human imperfection. 1 John 1:8 speaks to the self-deception regarding sin, while James 3:2 highlights the inevitability of offending others, particularly through speech. Together, they underscore the universal struggle with sin and the need for self-awareness.', 'theme', 0.58, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 8, 23, 53, 6, 6, 'we have no sin', 'Sin and Iniquity Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of human sinfulness. Both passages emphasize the reality of sin, with 1 John stating that we deceive ourselves about our sin, while Isaiah acknowledges that all have gone astray and have iniquity laid upon them.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 8, 62, 2, 4, 4, 'the truth is not in us', 'Connection of Truth and Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of truth and deception. The first verse discusses self-deception regarding sin, while the second addresses deception in claiming knowledge of God without obedience to His commandments.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 8, 18, 15, 14, 14, 'we have no sin', 'Human Sinfulness and Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the inherent sinfulness of humanity. 1 John 1:8 suggests that claiming to be without sin is self-deception, while Job 15:14 questions the possibility of human righteousness.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 8, 20, 20, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection on Sin and Purity', 'Both passages emphasize the acknowledgment of sin. 1 John 1:8 states that claiming to be without sin is self-deception, while Proverbs 20:9 questions who can claim purity from sin. This connection highlights the universal struggle with sin and the importance of honesty about one''s spiritual state.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 9, 19, 32, 5, 5, NULL, 'Connection of Confession and Forgiveness', 'Both passages emphasize the act of confession and the resulting forgiveness from God. 1 John 1:9 states that God is faithful to forgive when sins are confessed, while Psalms 32:5 recounts the acknowledgment of sin and the assurance of forgiveness.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 9, 20, 28, 13, 13, 'confess our sins', 'Confession and Forgiveness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of confessing sins to receive mercy and forgiveness. 1 John 1:9 highlights God''s faithfulness in forgiving those who confess, while Proverbs 28:13 states that confessing and forsaking sins leads to mercy.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 9, 24, 33, 8, 8, 'cleanse us from all unrighteousness', 'Forgiveness and Cleansing Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the themes of cleansing and forgiveness of sins. 1 John 1:9 speaks of being cleansed from all unrighteousness, while Jeremiah 33:8 mentions cleansing from all iniquity and pardoning transgressions.', 'theme', 0.9789999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 9, 19, 51, 2, 5, NULL, 'Confession and Cleansing Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the need for confession and the promise of cleansing from sin. 1 John 1:9 speaks of forgiveness and cleansing, while Psalms 51:2-5 expresses a plea for cleansing and acknowledgment of transgressions.', 'theme', 0.7969999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 9, 62, 1, 7, 7, NULL, 'Connection of Forgiveness and Cleansing', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of cleansing from sin. 1 John 1:9 speaks of being cleansed from all unrighteousness, while 1 John 1:7 mentions the blood of Jesus Christ cleansing us from all sin. This connection highlights the assurance of forgiveness and purification through Christ.', 'theme', 0.748, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 9, 26, 36, 25, 25, 'cleanse us from all unrighteousness', 'Cleansing and Forgiveness Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the act of cleansing from sin. 1 John 1:9 speaks of being cleansed from unrighteousness, while Ezekiel 36:25 mentions being cleansed from filthiness. This connection highlights the theme of divine forgiveness and purification.', 'theme', 0.608, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 9, 58, 10, 23, 23, 'he is faithful', 'Faithfulness of God', 'This connection highlights the faithfulness of God in both passages. In 1 John 1:9, God is described as faithful to forgive, while Hebrews 10:23 emphasizes that He is faithful to His promises.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 10, 62, 1, 8, 8, 'we have not sinned', 'Connection of Sin and Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of self-deception regarding sin. They highlight that claiming to be without sin leads to a false understanding of oneself and God''s truth.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 10, 62, 5, 10, 10, 'make him a liar', 'Connection of Truth and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of making God a liar when one denies truth. In 1 John 1:10, denying sin equates to calling God a liar, while 1 John 5:10 connects disbelief in God''s record of His Son to the same accusation.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 10, 19, 130, 3, 3, 'sinned', 'Sin and Accountability', 'Both passages emphasize the reality of sin and the consequences of denying it. 1 John 1:10 suggests that claiming sinlessness makes one a liar, while Psalms 130:3 questions who can stand if iniquities are marked by the Lord.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 10, 63, 1, 2, 2, 'his word is not in us', 'Connection of Truth and Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of truth within believers. In 1 John, acknowledging sin is crucial for the truth to dwell in us, as stated in 2 John.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 1, 10, 51, 3, 16, 16, 'his word is not in us', 'Connection of Sin and Word', 'This connection highlights the importance of acknowledging sin and the presence of God''s word in believers. Both passages emphasize the necessity of having the word of Christ dwell in us, which counters the claim of being without sin.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
