(62, 4, 5, 61, 2, 2, 3, 'the world heareth them', 'Connection of Worldly Influence', 'This connection highlights the theme of worldly influence and deception. Both passages address how those aligned with the world lead others astray, causing the truth to be misrepresented.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 4, 5, 19, 17, 4, 4, NULL, 'Worldly Influence and Guidance', 'This connection highlights the contrast between worldly influences and divine guidance. Both passages emphasize the importance of discernment in navigating the paths of life, with 1 John 4:5 noting the world''s voice and Psalms 17:4 referencing the protective power of God''s words.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 4, 5, 23, 30, 10, 11, 'the world heareth them', 'Worldly Influence on Prophecy', 'This connection highlights the rejection of true prophecy in favor of worldly desires. Both passages emphasize how those aligned with the world prefer messages that align with their own views, leading to a dismissal of genuine spiritual guidance.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 4, 5, 24, 5, 31, 31, 'they are of the world', 'Connection of False Prophets', 'Both passages emphasize the influence of worldly voices. In 1 John 4:5, those ''of the world'' speak and are heard, paralleling Jeremiah 5:31, where false prophets are accepted by the people. This connection highlights the theme of deception in spiritual leadership.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 4, 5, 55, 4, 3, 3, 'the world heareth them', 'Connection of Worldly Influence', 'This connection highlights the idea that those who speak from the world attract followers who desire teachings that align with their own desires. Both passages emphasize the influence of worldly perspectives on belief and doctrine.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(62, 4, 6, 43, 14, 17, 17, 'spirit of truth', 'Connection of Truth and Knowledge', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of the ''Spirit of truth'' and the distinction between those who know God and those who do not. This connection highlights how knowledge of God is linked to the reception of the Spirit of truth.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
